<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#D5E6E1"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#000080" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Thkeron Doomsayer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I remember reading many posts on this subject earlier, and almost noone seems to be using it in battles.<P>During the last week i've been spending alot of time in Sol B, more specifically the King/Priest/Champion area, and there are usually a bunch of lvl 46+ warriors there as well.<P>I know that the casting time of CH is 10 seconds, but i've found that if i start casting when the tank has hit 2 bubs, he rarely drops below 1.5 bubs, and so far has never dropped below 1.<P>And given that they have around 2.6K hp with buffs, it beats the crap outta superiour for mana efficiency.<P>It's quite possible that this tactic will begin to loose its usefullness when the mobs starts to hit lvl 49 or so as they hit alot harder then...but there will also be higher lvl buffs to hand out then...so *shrug*.<P>Any lvl 44+ clerics out there that uses CH in battles vs lvl 47+ mobs?<P><P>------------------<BR>Thkeron Doomsayer<BR>High Priest of Innoruuk<BR>Realm of Quellious<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Raanyar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I have also used CH in the bugs/bats area in Sol B. I should stress that I only use it after many pulls with the same group so that I can estimate the right time to do so. But with a fully buffed lvl 50 warrior - it's well worth it.<BR><P>------------------<BR>Raanyar T'Caledor<BR>Level 44 Cleric<BR>Cazic Thule Server<P><BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Badaf</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yes, in the right situation CH is the best way to go. This brings up debates of long ago concerning how monks (and rangers even) made better tanks. How many 45+ level clerics cast CH on a monk or ranger thats taking all the hits? Very few. Sure you might cast it after a battle and they are really low in HPs but usually not. Their hps just drop too fast in combat (in most situations)  for CH to be used safely.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dalain</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">My opinion of CH in battle is only if we are fighting a single mob.  Otherwise I think I risk the other tanks and/or casters if I'm tied up for 10 secs healing 1 person.  If more then 1 person is taking damage 10 secs to heal 1 of them is an awful long time, especially if they are a caster type.  In plane of fear or hate I've seen a caster drop in 3 rounds which is < 10 secs, heck that's even less then the time for a superior heal. Last night in Hate I saw my first insta tank nuke, non-lag related.  Monk was alive, 3 mobs inc, before I could stand up and hit my heal hot key, monk dead.  <IMG SRC="http://www.kmrcs.com/eqcleric/ultbbs/ubb/frown.gif">  Oh well, nobody else died.  But there are times when I will use CH in battle, but multi mob fights just isn't 1 of them (usually).<P>Dalain</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Beene</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Well I have spent alot of time at lvl 50 as a cleric. About 22 days worth i think now. That is half as long as it took me to get to 50 so ive had alot of time to play with differant spells and how they work. I have had warriors past 3000 hps so if you think about it if i CH him at half im still saving mana over superior heal. Warriors are really the only person who CH is useful for in normal day situations unless you are using Symbol and then it may be helpful on others. You just have to <BR>1) Know the are well and know the creatures and thier damage output very well. <BR>2) Know who you are fighting with and hope they trust you enough to let thier health drop down past half. <BR>3) Not lagging badly. Any lag could cause an untimely death. <BR><P>------------------<BR>Beene, Cleric of Bristlebane<BR>Officer of Combine (karana</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Lucretia</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I don't use CH on just warriors.  Any buffed melee class over 1800 hp can benefit.  SH heals around 700, from what I've read.  So if a player at 1800 hp receives a CH at 2 bubbles, that's 1080 hp healed, which saves you an additional cast of a GH, which with the SH would end up costing you the same as CH.  Also, casting one healing spell instead of two, will taunt mobs less.  Most melee types once they reach the high 40's or 50 will have at least 2000hp when buffed with symbol.<P>I don't use CH on casters because they take damage much more quickly.  AC, stats, caps on things such as dodge, and the absence of skills such as parry, etc. contribute to this.  In fact, I usually still use GH on most casters since I want something fast.<P>I use CH a lot on my main tank, who just happens to be a ranger.  I even use it when fighting hard hitting mobs such as nox.  There's a limit though.  I would never use it if he was being attacked by multiple mobs at once or if we were fighting a hard-hitting creature like the ones in Fear or Hate.<P>It's a great spell if you have the sense to know when to use it.<P><P>------------------<BR>Lucretia Rialsq<BR>Cleric of Tunare<BR>Bristlebane <P></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
